Expression Set Action for Integration Procedures

An Expression Set Action invokes the specified Expression Set and returns the results to the Integration Procedure.

As an alternative, you can call an Expression Set using a Remote Action. Follow the steps in Access Legacy Calculation Procedures and Matrices, but set isExpressionSet to true.

NOTE You can ignore a Calculation Procedure: Not Found error when exporting an Integration Procedure that calls an Expression Set.

An Integration Procedure invokes an Expression Set, which invokes a Decision Matrix. TheÂ Expression Set applies a 15% discount to a quoted amount for an Age from 16 to 24 and a GPA of 3.0 or greater.
